📊 Customer Churn Prediction (Advanced Machine Learning Project)
📌 Overview
This project predicts whether a customer will churn (leave a service) using machine learning techniques.

It is designed as a real-world business problem commonly faced in industries like telecom, SaaS, and subscription-based services.

🎯 Problem statment
Customer churn directly impacts business revenue. Companies need to identify customers who are likely to leave so they can take preventive actions.

The objective of this project is to:

Predict customer churn

Identify key factores influencing churn

Improve customer retention strategies

🧠 Machine Learning Workflow
This project follows a complete ML pipeline:

📊 1. DAta Preprocessing
NUmerical + categorical features

Feature Scaling using StandardScaler

Encoding categorical variables using OneHotEncoding

🤖 2. Models Used
Logistic Regression (baseline model)

Random Forest Classifier (advanced model)

⚙️ 3. Model Optimization
pipeline-based training
Model comparison
Improved performance using ensemble methods
📈 4. Evaluation Matrics
Accuracy Score
Classification report (Precision, Recall, F1-score)
ROC Curve
AUC Curve
🔍 5. Feature Analysis
Feature importance from Random Forest
Identification of key churn drivers
📊 Key Results
Random Forest performed better than Logistic Regression

ROC-AUC score indicates strong predictive performance

Most important features affecting churn:

Monthly Charges

Tenure

Contact type

💡 Business Insights
Customers with high monthly charges and low tenure are more likely to churn
Month-to-month contracts have higher churn risk
Long-term customers are more stable and valuable
📌 Business Impact
Identify at-risk customers early

Reduce customer loss

Improve retention strategies

Increase company revenue

